HEADWORD: Esnecy
<hw>Es"ne*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Eigne</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A prerogative given to
the eldest coparcener to choose first after an inheritance is
divided.</def> <rj><au>Mozley & W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

